\cf0 Prior to establishing Lotka&Co, Lauren co-founded ARTIFECT, a consulting agency focused on in-house talent needs, brand building tactics, and investment prospects for designers and brands globally.  Notable achievements include securing Kate Spade\'92s first ever global outerwear license, investing in luxury eveningwear designer Elizabeth Kennedy, and placing exceptional talent in coveted positions at Calvin Klein, The Row, Urban Zen and ADEAM.\
Prior to starting her own agencies, Lauren was recruited to launch Creative Management Agency.  As the Managing Director, Lauren built an agency that parlayed business development + brand strategy with a talent acquisition division. In the first year, Lauren grew the team from 3 to 18, executed licensing deals for Nicole Miller and Amerex Group, and built an executive search practice servicing clients such as IPPOLITA, Kellwood, NY&Co, and Burch Creative Capital.\
Lauren\'92s formative years in fashion started at DMA where she worked as an agent and business development lead.  She represented the likes of Alexander McQueen, Pamela Love, celebrity stylist Leslie Fremar and supermodel Veronica Webb.  Some of her executed deals include Tucker for Target, Pamela Love x TopShop, Tracy Hutson for QVC, and Leslie Fremar for Fruit of the Loom.\
